output.crosstab_text:
For first degree graduates of English studies, one year after graduation, Wholesale and retail trade - repair of motor vehicles and motorcycles was the most common industry for White ethnicity graduates, Administrative and support service activities, Professional, scientific and technical activities and Wholesale and retail trade - repair of motor vehicles and motorcycles were the most common industries for Black ethnicity graduates, Administrative and support service activities, Education and Wholesale and retail trade - repair of motor vehicles and motorcycles were the most common industries for Asian and Not known ethnicity graduates, Education and Information and communication were the most common industries for Mixed ethnicity graduates, and Accommodation and food service activities, Administrative and support service activities, Education, Information and communication, Professional, scientific and technical activities and Wholesale and retail trade - repair of motor vehicles and motorcycles were the most common industries for Other ethnicity graduates.

The industry with the largest range in proportions was Accommodation and food service activities where Other ethnicity graduates had the highest proportion and Black ethnicity graduates had the lowest proportion. The industry with the largest range in median earnings was Administrative and support service activities where Mixed ethnicity graduates had the highest median earnings (£20,500) and Black ethnicity graduates had the lowest median earnings (£13,200). The group with the highest earnings was Asian ethnicity graduates who worked in the Financial and insurance activities industry (median earnings of £22,700).
output.crosstab_title: Industry of graduate employment for graduates of English studies by ethnicity, one year after graduation, male and female first degree graduates from English HEIs, APs and FECs, 2019/20 tax year.
